eNCA's Devan Murugan unpacks the confusion around a tweet from government's primary Twitter account on cigarette and alcohol sales. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Sent out around midday on Wednesday, the tweet on government's primary Twitter account said cigarette and alcohol sales will remain banned as long as South Africa is in lockdown. Then, at about 5pm, GCIS said this was an error. It meant to point out that the alcohol and cigarette ban was in place for lockdown level 3. SA Lockdown:Â Restaurants protest restrictions The alcohol ban alone is said to put one million jobs at stake. On the tax front, advisory group Mazars says if both the tobacco and alcohol bans are upheld until the end of the year, total losses could reach R30-billion. Watch the video above for more on this story